, 
<figureCitation box="[270,326,582,608]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 6" captionStart-1="FIGURE 7" captionStart-2="FIGURE 8" captionStart-3="FIGURE 9" captionStart-4="FIGURE 10" captionStartId-0="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionStartId-2="8.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionStartId-3="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionStartId-4="10.[151,250,1119,1143]" captionTargetBox-0="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetBox-1="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetBox-2="[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetBox-3="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,181,1095]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetId-1="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetId-2="figure-78@8.[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetId-3="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId-4="figure-26@10.[151,1436,181,1095]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="8" captionTargetPageId-3="9" captionTargetPageId-4="10" captionText-0="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." captionText-1="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." captionText-2="FIGURE 8. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." captionText-3="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." captionText-4="FIGURE 10. Map of Capanema gen. nov. species geographical records." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119806" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119812" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5119806/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5119812/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">6–10</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
