<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="559" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,654,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tegmina with distal region concave (
<figureCitation box="[711,782,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Fourth branch of vein CuA and vein MP connected by transverse vein (
<figureCitation box="[335,403,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). First branch of vein CuA associated with hyaline regions with dark bands lined up (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1422,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Lateral lobes of mesobasisternum forming an acute posterolateral angle of 50° straight (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1244,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Apex of cercus with rounded expansion and small spiny (
<figureCitation box="[618,708,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="559" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" box="[199,535,798,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,535,798,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
Description. 
<typeStatus box="[352,461,798,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Holotype</typeStatus>
Male.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis box="[199,280,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Thorax</emphasis>
. Lateral lobes of mesobasisternum anterolaterally, laterally and posteriorly straight, forming an acute posterolateral angle of 50° straight (
<figureCitation box="[555,642,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Metabasisternum triangular, anteriorly straight and laterally with two small convex projections (
<figureCitation box="[446,534,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" box="[199,1380,942,969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis box="[199,267,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Wings</emphasis>
. Tegmina wide, posterior margin and distal region convex (
<figureCitation box="[937,1005,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). MA with two branches (
<figureCitation box="[1298,1366,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
First branch of the CuA vein with hyaline region associated with small circular patches grouped, forming black stripes aligned laterally on both sides of the branch; other branches of CuA and MP with narrow hyaline region also with several small circular spots, forming asymmetrical spots (
<figureCitation box="[847,915,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Fourth branch of vein CuA and vein MP connected by transverse vein (
<figureCitation box="[450,519,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Vein CuA not connected with vein MP (
<figureCitation box="[986,1055,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,189,763]" captionTargetId="figure-26@8.[205,1382,181,771]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
Total length of left stridulatory file 
<quantity box="[598,665,1122,1149]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="559" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, greater vein width of 0.4 mm and a total of 49 teeth. Right stridulatory file slightly curved, with apex region concave (
<figureCitation box="[743,833,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-78@8.[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Total length file of 1.8 mm, widest vein of 0.2 mm and total of 51 teeth. Teeth rectangular, narrow and far apart; teeth basal minor; in basal half larger and more widely spaced (
<figureCitation box="[243,377,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-78@8.[213,1375,915,1979]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 8A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1266,1292]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Apex of cercus with rounded expansion and small spiny, both with dark brown coloration (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis box="[199,464,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Internal male genitalia.</emphasis>
Ejaculatory vesicle reniform (
<figureCitation box="[802,937,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9A–D</figureCitation>
). Upper fold of ventral lobe large, elongated, asymetrical and not connected (
<figureCitation box="[519,658,1374,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9A–B</figureCitation>
). Titillator process large and asymetrical (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1285,1374,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9A–D</figureCitation>
). Lower fold of ventral lobe large, posteriorly convex and exceeding the dorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[972,1109,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9A–B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal lobe anteriorly with median convex projection, laterally with two long and acuminated projections, posteriorly convex (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1424,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9A–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal fold elongated and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[543,678,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[173,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1331]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., male internal genitalia. A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view; E: phallus with titillator sclerite, ventral view; F: titillator sclerite. Abbreviations: AP: sclerites of apodemes; DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TS: titillator sclerite; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119810/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Figs. 9C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" box="[199,1288,1518,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis box="[199,330,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Coloration.</emphasis>
Based on photos of preserved specimen (
<figureCitation box="[795,864,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[245,1350,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[234,1353,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Capanema pocanga sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Body yellowish-green. Eyes brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" box="[199,408,1554,1580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Female: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="559" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1590,1616]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet is in apposition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" box="[674,770,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Capanema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pocanga">
<emphasis box="[674,770,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">pocanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[pokanga] comes from the Brazilian indigenous language Tupi and means “which is rare”, in reference to the rarity of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1904]" box="[199,783,1662,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,1662,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Geographical records.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[472,545,1662,1688]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[553,671,1662,1688]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[687,770,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1119,1143]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[151,1436,181,1095]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Map of Capanema gen. nov. species geographical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119812/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="559">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
